Week 3

Access modifiers

visibility and accessibility 

class, methods, constructors variable 

Types:

public  - anywhere class, any package
protected - same class, sub class, same package (diff package - extend the class)
private - only within the declared class (most protected)
default - class, within same package


Non Access modifiers

final, static, abstract  //  synchronized(imp), transient, volatile

Final - cant override (final pi = 3.14;)

static - belongs to class, not specific to object, we can call without creating and object

Abstract - abstract method - directly belongs to abstract class 

public abstract void run();  //declaration 


ABSTRACT CLASS: 

its a restricted ( that cant object )

declaration methods(both abstract and default) and variables 

public abstract void run();  //declaration 

abstract class Animal{
   name;
   public abstract void animalSound();  //declaration 
   public void hunting(){
    ....
    ....
   }
   Animal a = new Animal(); //error
}

class Tiger extends Animal{

    public void animalSound(){
        sysout(" ytjhbih" );

     }
    //override hunting
}

 Peacock extends Animal{

    public void animalSound(){
        sysout(" hgbkhrfug" );

     }
    //override hunting
    No hunting
}


